The increase in production in the eurozone slowed to its lowest point in the last 13 months in August, according to a closely watched study.
The final Markit Purchasing Managers' Index of Manufacturing (PMI) fell to 50.7 in August, down from 51.8 in July.
A figure above 50 indicates an expansion.
New orders declined and factories experienced slumps at a time of rising tensions between the EU and Russia over Ukraine.
